}}{{TIDTOC|adapter}} ==Overview== "M01-UFEHL-X10" is silkscreened on the board of a production model USB10T (S/N: 015054370, Ver: C1). :The FCC ID noted on the device is MQ4USB10TA.. but this adapter is actuality an '''AboCom''' UFE1000B.
Note: '''Linksys''''s drivers appear to have 4 USB IDs for KLSI devices. It may be possible a '''KLSI''' USB10T was released. *07b8:4000 ('''AboCom''' ID) *066b:2202 ('''Linksys''' ID) *05e9:0008 (default KL5KUSB101B ID?) *0565:0005 ('''Pericom''' ID)
